Kenneth Morgan Stancil III, 20, was arrested around 1.30 a.m. on Tuesday when he was seen sleeping in Daytona Beach, Florida .
Stancil, a third-year student at the college, had a knife with him when he allegedly shot dead his former work-study supervisor Ron Lane .
He was arrested without incident when Volusia County beach patrol officers found him sleeping on the beach, which is a violation of a local ordinance .
Police are investigating the fatal shooting as a possible hate crime, although they refuse to say what hate crime is .